canonical:
  title: 元日
  author: 金訢
  language: lzh
  text: 門戶何曾施欝壘杯盤未見頌椒花家貧自是輕佳節唯覺年華上鬢華
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 元日
  author: 金訢
  language: lzh
  text: 門戶何曾施欝壘。杯盤未見頌椒花。家貧自是輕佳節。唯覺年華上鬢華。
korean:
  title: 원일
  author: 김흔
  language: kor
  text: |-
    문호에 어찌 일찍 울루를 두었던가
    배반은 보지 못하고 추화를 외우노라
    집이 가난하매 지금부터는 가절을 가벼이 여기리니
    오직 세월이 흰밑 살쩍털에 오르는 것만 깨닫으리라
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1450_020_0850&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: New Year's Day
  author: Kim Hyn
  language: eng
  text: |-
    What need have I for festive decorations at my door?
    I have no wine cups filled, no fragrant peppercorn flowers to praise.
    In poverty, I've learned to make light of such celebrations—
    I only feel the years climbing into the white hairs of my temples.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: The 'peppercorn flowers' (椒花) reference alludes to traditional New Year festivities and abundance
  - key: ''
    value: White hairs are a traditional metaphor for the passage of time and aging in East Asian poetry
